    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@mmmh81 actually that is how I got to this issue and started noticing this pattern. I have seen this before and I actually experienced this myself while building my own RTS engine.\n\nPathfinding wise, you could have the naive heuristic saying shrouded areas are always passable. Of course, when traversing the path a unit encounters some non-passable entities/terrain and your path finder kicks in again. This might be a bit expensive, but 'first make it work then fast'. (making fast could be doing partial path finding till the next node in your path you where unable to reach?)\n"
  },
