    "created_at": "2016-01-03T17:20:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-03T17:20:20Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm not sure where I read this, but have you considered to not do path finding? I'm not sure about how C&C does this, but I believe the behavior there is to have an optimistic 'shortest direction' movement. Ie, no path finding, just take the best cell to move to. Until you hit an obstacle and only then calculate a path.\n\nPerhaps it might help in this case, although it still requires a layered way of approaching path finding. It also is perf-wise much faster because you don't do path finding at all at first. \n\nAlso hitting a unit is not considered an obstacle to use path finding for. \n"
